Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve any large @broccoli florets{200} and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and the @Thai style spice mix{1} (use less if you'd prefer things milder). Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the broccoli roasts, pour the cold @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{0.25%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Zest and cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and sliced pepper to the pan and season with salt and pepper. Cook until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir in the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} to coat and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}, then stir to combine. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened.

Simmer the curry until the pepper and chicken are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the roasted broccoli through the chicken curry, then remove from the heat and stir in the @soy sauce{15%g}. Squeeze in some lime juice.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork and stir through the lime zest.

Share the zesty rice between your #bowls and top with the Thai style chicken curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!